<Layout
  title="About — Gabriela Stoloff-Báez"
  description="Biography of soprano Gabriela Stoloff-Báez: Oberlin Conservatory and San Francisco Conservatory training, performances with Opera Parallèle, Opera Theatre of St. Louis, and Seraphic Fire."
  type="profile"
>
  <Page title="About" lead="Soprano · Oberlin Conservatory · San Francisco Conservatory of Music">
    <p>
      Gabriela Stoloff-Báez is a Puerto Rican soprano whose performances span opera,
      oratorio, and contemporary art song. She holds a Bachelor of Music from the
      Oberlin Conservatory of Music and a Master of Music from the San Francisco
      Conservatory of Music.
    </p>

    <p>
      Recent engagements include performances with Opera Parallèle, Opera Theatre of
      St. Louis, and Seraphic Fire. She was named a 2023 Oregon District winner of
      the Metropolitan Opera's Laffont Competition and the 2024 recipient of the
      Elihu Hyndman Memorial Award. In summer 2026 she joins Des Moines Metro Opera
      as an Apprentice Artist.
    </p>

    <p>
      Her artistic practice is centered on repertoire that celebrates diversity,
      multiplicity, social justice, and humanity.
    </p>

    <h2>Press &amp; Bookings</h2>
    <p>
      For management inquiries, press requests, and a downloadable EPK,
      <a href="/contact/">please get in touch</a>.
    </p>
  </Page>
</Layout>
